# Unit Test Update Policy

- When implementing feature or refactor requests, do not proactively edit unit test files (`*.spec.ts`, `*.test.ts`).
- If existing tests fail after code changes, report the failure and ask whether tests should be updated.
- Only modify unit tests when the user explicitly asks to:
  - update tests,
  - fix failing tests,
  - or add new tests.
- Keep this policy lower priority only than direct user instructions in the current chat.
